'''''Photobacterium leiognathi''''' is a species of [[Gram-negative bacteria]]. The species is [[bioluminescence|bioluminescent]] and a [[symbiosis|symbiont]] of [[ponyfish]] (family Leiognathidae).<ref>{{cite journal|last=LEE|first=Chan Yong|author2=SZITTNER, Rose B. |author3=MEIGHEN, Edward A. |title=The lux gene of the luminous bacterial symbiont, ''Photobacterium leiognathi'', of the ponyfish. Nucleotide sequence, difference in gene organization, and high expression in mutant ''Escherichia coli''|journal=European Journal of Biochemistry|date=October 1991|volume=201|issue=1|pages=161–167|doi=10.1111/j.1432-1033.1991.tb16269.x}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Dunlap|first=Paul V.|title=Osmotic control of luminescence and growth in ''Photobacterium leiognathi'' from ponyfish light organs|journal=Archives of Microbiology|date=February 1985|volume=141|issue=1|pages=44–50|doi=10.1007/BF00446738}}</ref>

